This paper proposes a data-to-text generation model that uses two modules for tracking and text generation. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and specifically, text generation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses machine learning techniques such as conditioning and memorization, which are common in artificial intelligence (AI) research, making cs.AI another likely sub-category. The model also involves selecting and determining intermediate variables, which are common in machine learning and deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions content planning and surface realization, which are related to information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper uses a neural network for generation, which is a common technique in neural engineering (cs.NE).
